> Does anyone know if there is a tool to be had that fits the two notches in the dashboard switch (lights, wiper, etc.) mounting bezels so you can easily screw them on and off?? The best I've been able to come up with is needle nose pliers, and that ain't so good.
> 
> Rusty

I've had good luck with putting a penny in my vise grips. The penny 
matches the curve of the escutcheons quite well. Of course, this only 
works for the switches to don't have the post sticking out.

Hope this helps,
